description.narrative: UNICEF advocacy and technical support improved the positioning of nutrition on the national priority agenda. Technical and financial support for treatment of severe acute malnutrition (SAM) including procurement of life-saving therapeutic food enabled 32% increase in SAM coverage across the country with 82% treatment recovery rate. Reaching 96% of children of 6-59 months old with vitamin A contributed to reducing micronutrient deficiency in children under 5 years, towards improving the nutrition status of children in the country. UNICEF support enabled the progressive implementation of salt iodization law and gaps and bottlenecks analysis and recommended solutions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
